snippet.textDisplay: Pains me to say it, as a blade, but I think Wednesday were hard done by here. 100% that goal gets reviewed and potentially chalked off for offside in a premier league stadium, given the offsides that have been given this season with VAR. snippet.textDisplay:
As a Wednesday fan, I am pleased with how we defended.
Had we not pressured them as much as we did, it could easily been a whole lot worse.

Shame we lost, and what kind of goal we lost to (unfortunate for Joe), but to be honest I'm not even angry.
They did their best and fell short. All we ask, as fans, is that the players give their all and they did that tonight against a Manchester City side that had a lot of their strongest players starting or on the bench.
snippet.textOriginal:
As a Wednesday fan, I am pleased with how we defended.
Had we not pressured them as much as we did, it could easily been a whole lot worse.

Shame we lost, and what kind of goal we lost to (unfortunate for Joe), but to be honest I'm not even angry. 
They did their best and fell short. All we ask, as fans, is that the players give their all and they did that tonight against a Manchester City side that had a lot of their strongest players starting or on the bench.
